CHIKUNGUNYA - INDIAN OCEAN UPDATE (13): INDIA (KERALA)
***********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: 21 Jun 2007
Source: The Hindu [edited]
<http://www.hindu.com/2007/06/21/stories/2007062158280300.htm>

So far, 532 suspected cases of chikungunya have been reported in the
district this year [2007]. Suspected chikungunya cases were reported
from Manambur, Vellanad, Vellarada, Perumkadavila, Nedumangad,
Neyyattinkara and Attingal; 7 medical camps were conducted, which
were attended by 1478 patients. Of these, 144 reported with fever.
Camps will be held at Poovachal and Shanghumughom on Thursday [21 Jun
2007].
--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Brent Barrett
[ProMED requests information about measures being taken to control
the mosquito vector, most likely _Aedes aegypti_, in the affected
area and about how dengue and chikungunya cases are being
differentiated.
A map of India can be accessed at
<http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/middle_east_and_asia/india_pol01.jpg>,
and a map of Kerala, showing districts, at
<http://www.naturemagics.com/kerala-maps/kerala-map.shtm>.
- Mod.TY]
